description: The M stands for Murder, Mystery, and Mayhem in this collection of stories from fan favorite Bret M. Herholz! This collection includes: Diary of the Black Widow, Confessions of a Peculiar Boy, The Adventures of Polly and Handgraves, The Spaghetti Strand Murder

volume.name: Murder, Mystery, & Mayhem: The Bret M. Herholz Collection

description: Nobody Can Eat 50 Eggs #1 is choke full of colorful humorous comics and illustrated features in the vein of MAD magazine. Warning signs your boss is an alien, lonely yeti, dead superheroes, how to survive robot world domination, and common mistakes dumb pirates do are all part of the fun in this 36 page comic book by Steve Steiner.

This comic presents four real life stories from the world of sport. The characters are not big stars but down to earth individuals who, despite failing to achieve their goals, were able to convey essential qualities for the personal and social life of individuals. These pages contain commendable examples of self-improvement, effort, disinterested friendship, nobility, loyalty, humour and sportsmanship in defeat. All these virtues comprise some of the values sport should promote, much more important than a victory.
Candy is the only human girl in her class at a space-based school. When a mysterious new student arrives, will Candy discover a kindred spirit? Or continue to feel alienated among aliens?
Dysfunctional Families

Leo joined AmeriCorps to do something important with his life. When his team is sent to rebuild St. Bernard Parish after Hurricane Katrina, he believes he'll finally be able to make a difference in the world. But while other teams do the "real" work of gutting and rebuilding houses, Leo is assigned to the camp newsletter. His friends Snave, Cirelle, and Davy have equally unglamorous, minor jobs in the kitchen and supply rooms. Only Kiley, the girl Leo pines after, spends her days saving "da parish" from ruin. Frustrated, Leo and his friends chafe against authority and each other in a town longing for renewal. They're all looking for something. Or running from something. Often, both.

Remorse is a tragic-comic about a young Dubliner who takes a turn down the wrong corridor and ends up working in a call-center for an entire decade. Step into a world of cubicles, vending machines, broken hearts and photocopiers; hold music, nightmares and missed opportunities.

If you were ever young and foolish, this is for you.

Rowdy Roddy Piper was a man of many talents - wrestler, storyteller, monster killer. Get the real scoop about Rod's life, his mission, and the way he was secretly saving humanity for over 30 years. Wrestling may have given him the cover, but Rod's real job wasn't something he chose - it was handed down to him by his ancestors. Now Rod has to pass the torch - or the shillelagh - along to his son, Colt, who thinks Rod abandoned him, and who wants nothing to do with him. With a cover by renowned artist Joe Jusko, incredible interior art and a story you can't put down, this graphic novel is sure to be a collector's item for generations.

Note: The digital edition (10/14/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: GN

description: When a dinosaur is abducted by aliens, he receives the gift of rationality and goes on many adventures in space. Follow our Cretaceous hero as he tells the tale of how he becomes a star explorer and his search for the most important thing in his existence; the way back home. This is the origin of Space Parasaurolophus: The Living Fossil.

Driven by greed, on the edge of the law, their business is blood. They are the killers, the assassins, the merciless trackers of the underworld, and if you're their enemy, you're probably dead. Remember, a bounty hunter only follows the Rule of Gold.

Note: The digital edition (10/14/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Provenance

Atum is a young man whose life is a constant balance between his personal quest for freedom and maintaining a relationship with his demanding father. We meet Atum, 15 years old, as he rises out of the "Family Pool," a place where ancestors judge their descendants and bestow special powers upon them. Atum's father, Auberon, is a dethroned tyrant who hopes to use Atum's new powers to regain his throne.
name: Provenance

description:
Legend of Thunder Valley

Thunder-Valley 1890

In the pristine and bountiful heart of Thunder Valley, a tribe of Indians is attempting to find their own place within the natural way. Made up of several different tribes and bands, they've left the reservation's confines and attempt to live on the land as their ancestors once did.

The mysterious forces that swirl and pulsate in Thunder-Valley can give great gifts, but they can also spawn the most horrible creatures and tragedies imaginable. The Thunder-Beings, the spirits tasked with overseeing this rift, this churning fountain of creation, have become complacent. Their neglect of the order has left the great machine of life unattended. Energy slips out and sometimes pours into the valley. Thoughts and hopes, fears and desire gift life to evils that never knew life. Long dead gods find power.

The gods here are as real as the horrors and triumphs in and around Thunder-Valley. In fact, through the dreams and nightmares of the living, new gods are born everyday. One of those creatures, and tragedies, is "Vile" Clem Styles. However, this is the story of one of the lost souls that encounters him.
name: Legend of Thunder Valley

description:
The Beginning

The Villain has already won. He has already exacted his revenge on the superheroes of Legend City. Galaxy, once called "The Champion of Legend City", is the only hero who was allowed to live. He returns after 5 years of exile to tell the villain that tonight is the night he will die.
name: The Beginning
